      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEZA PUNK ROCKER NZ (4) showed good improvement second-up when he raced parked from this barrier but proved too good with a 4.6m win in the Victor Harbor Cup last start. Has won two of three previous third-up attempts so should be at his peak. Can strike again. LORD ZARIAS NZ (3) came from the back row for second to Heza Punk Rocker in the Victor Harbor Cup last start. Better drawn and strikes at 50 per cent at this circuit and distance. Race fit now and could turn the tables. DHAULAGIRI NZ (7) draws for a trail and has claims off a Globe Derby win three back. Tricky draw for LAST TANGO IN HEAVEN NZ (11) but he has worked his way back into peak form, winning last start at Gawler.",
